reviewText: I first saw this movie on TV.  The second time it aired, I recorded it.  The third time, I just had to purchase it.  It is a wonderful movie about how busy we can get, but it is not too late to redirect what is important and that is our family.
Title: Christmas at Water's Edge

reviewText: THIS DVD MOVIE WAS ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL!! IT WAS WELL ACTED, WELL PRODUCED & WELL WRITTEN!!!! I TRULY ENJOYED THIS MOVIE FROM BEGINNING TO END!! I WISH IT COULD HAVE BEEN LONGER! (LOL) THIS MOVIE WAS A BLESSING & A LESSON LEARNED THAT I WILL SHARE AND RECOMMEND TO FAMILY & FRIENDS!! THE CAST WAS SIMPLY AWESOME & OUTSTANDING!!!!  I WILL WATCH THIS MOVIE OVER & OVER AGAIN!!  CECELIA P. LOS ANGELES, CA.

reviewText: An exciting movie about a young angel and a spoiled rich girl, who come together to save an area of their town.  Moving.

reviewText: This movie was very refreshing and teaches the meaning of Christmas, spreading God's Love with others and selflessness. Pooch and Keshia did a wonderful job.  This is a great family movie and fun to watch.
Title: Christmas at Water's Edge

reviewText: I think Keshia and "fine thang" are great in this movie together.  She's has a fun, upbeat energy and he's just cool!  It's on my list to watch every Christmas.  It's a feel-good movie that's nice to watch during the holidays.  Tom Bosley was a nice surprise. I had not seen him since Happy Days!  It was easy for me to watch because I could relate to the family's economic status better than most black movies. No profanity. No "over done" romantic scenes.  Good family movie for all!
Title: Christmas at Water's Edge
